From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
Date: Sat, 26 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: intel-nvme-remap: NULL-check devm_kzalloc

zen/0002 imports the Intel remapped-NVMe controller driver. Its probe
calls devm_kzalloc and immediately dereferences the result through
nrdev->sysdata.domain etc. without checking for an OOM failure. With
GFP_KERNEL the allocation is rarely going to fail in practice, but a
NULL-deref under memory pressure is a stupid way to lose the boot path
on a system whose only block device is the remapped NVMe behind this
controller.

---
 drivers/pci/controller/intel-nvme-remap.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/intel-nvme-remap.c b/drivers/pci/controller/intel-nvme-remap.c
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/intel-nvme-remap.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/intel-nvme-remap.c
@@ -524,6 +524,8 @@ static int nvme_remap_probe(struct pci_dev *dev,
 	struct pci_dev *child;

 	nrdev = devm_kzalloc(&dev->dev, sizeof(*nrdev), GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!nrdev)
+		return -ENOMEM;
 	nrdev->sysdata.domain = find_free_domain();
 	nrdev->sysdata.nvme_remap_dev = dev;
 	nrdev->dev = dev;
--
2.52.0
